I’d like to commend the president on his first State of the Union address tonight. We have much work ahead of us. It’s time to roll up our sleeves and get the job done. #SOTU

Let’s face it – we face threats from rogue nations and terrorist organizations alike. We must continue to dismantle ISIS and take a hard line against North Korea. We must keep our citizens safe. #SOTU
The opioid epidemic is very real. It's devastating communities in #Michigan and across the country. Working together we must continue our response to this crisis. #SOTU

Long supported common-sense immigration reforms. Hopeful we can take on the challenge & come to a long-term solution for DACA recipients coupled with more security for our borders. The president's framework takes steps in the right direction. #SOTU

Infrastructure is another issue where there is a clear need to build for the future. We are a nation of builders – whether it’s roads, bridges, highways or energy infrastructure. These efforts also help our economy. #SOTU

POTUS just mentioned breakthrough medical advances. We’re off to a good start with the 21st Century Cures Act but we must continue investing in our future in order to find cures for diseases that impact every family. #SOTU #CuresNow
